<body>

    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>
    <%- include('partials/layout')%>

    <div class="window" id="info-w1">
        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec1">
            <h1>I - Main Idea</h1>
            <p>
                Junto is a student-led community that aims
                to revive creativity, curiosity, and productivity
                among Iraqi youth. We provide spaces for students
                to express themselves, grow their skills,
                and connect with others — building a foundation for
                future leaders who will reshape our society
            </p>
            <p>
                Founders: Mohammed Hassan Raji &
                Mohammed Hassan Mahdi Misraa
            </p>
            <p>
                Founded: First semester 2024/2025 at the College of Medicine,
                University of Baghdad
            </p>
            <p>
                Origin: Started with four clubs to engage students in meaningful activities,
                 then expanded after seeing their potential.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec2">
            <h1>II - Identity</h1>
            <p>
                Name: Junto 
            </p>
            <p>   
                Mission: To restore lost cultural and intellectual values by giving youth a platform to create, learn, and lead through student-run clubs.
            </p>
            <p>
                Vision: To develop self-driven leaders who will rebuild their communities with creativity, knowledge, and cooperation.
            </p>
            <p>
                Core Values:
            </p>
            <p>
                Everyone You Meet Knows Something You Don’t.
            </p>
            <p>
                Consistency Is Your Greatest Achievement.
            </p>
            <p>
                Define Yourself Through What You Love.
            </p>
            <p>
                Set Weekly Goals.
            </p>
            <p>
                If You Teach Something, You Learn It Twice.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec3">
            <h1>III - Founders</h1>
            <p>
                The Founders are the original creators and permanent guardians of Junto’s mission and values.
                <br><br>
                Their role includes:
                <br>
                Approving all sponsorships, partnerships, or external offers before they take effect.

                Appointing and removing managers as needed.

                Overseeing any major changes to the mission, structure, or identity.

                Acting as the final authority on key organizational decisions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec4">
            <h1>IV - Leadership & Governance</h1>
            <p>
                <span class="chapters" id="ch-4-1">Managers 4.1</span>

            Currently, the Founders serve as the only managers.
            <br><br>
            Responsibilities:
            <br>
            Supporting club supervisors.

            Managing daily operations and growth plans.

            Making decisions on routine matters.
            <br><br>
            Future:
            <br>
            As Junto grows, more managers may be appointed by the founders.
            </p>
            <p>
                <span class="chapters" id="ch-4-2">Club Supervisors 4.2</span>
    
                Each club must have at least one supervisor.
                <br><br>
                Tasks:
                <br>
                Keep activities focused and engaging.
                
                Host at least one event weekly.
                
                Develop short- and long-term club plans.
                
                Supervisors facilitate and encourage, respecting diverse opinions related to the club’s focus.
                
                Supervisors are appointed by managers/founders.
                
                
            </p>
            <p>
                <span class="chapters" id="ch-4-3">Core Operations Team (COT) 4.3</span>
                
                Team responsible for design, development, media, and event support.

                Works closely with supervisors and managers.

                Handles branding, content, social media, and technical support.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec5">
            <h1>V - Clubs & Members</h1>
            <p>
                <span class="chapters" id="ch-5-1">Clubs 5.1</span>
                
                Current clubs:
                <br>
                Visual Art, Music, Book, History, Arabic, Movies, Gaming, STEM.
                <br><br>
                New clubs can be added with founders’ approval.
            </p>
            <p>
                <span class="chapters" id="ch-5-1">Members 5.2</span>
                
                Organized by university, club, and membership level.
                <br><br>
                Membership levels include:
                <br><br>
                Knowledge: Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced (self-assessed).
                <br><br>
                Activity: Active, Intermediate, Idle.
                <br><br>
                Inactive members get a warning after a week and may become mute members who receive updates but don’t participate.
               
                Active members can grow into leadership roles.
            </p>

        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec6">
            <h1>VI - Operations & Standards</h1>
            <p>
                Membership and event records maintained by the Core Operations Team.
                Events with external partners or funding require founder approval.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec7">
            <h1>VII - Partnerships & Sponsorships</h1>
            <p>
                All sponsorships and partnerships require explicit founder approval before commitment.
             
                Financial transparency maintained by managers/founders with regular reporting.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec8">
            <h1>VIII - Code of Conduct</h1>
            <p>
                Members must show respect, openness, and cooperation.
            
                Harassment or discrimination is not tolerated.
              
                Junto remains non-political; members should not use the platform for political agendas.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec9">
            <h1>IX - Decision Making & Dispute Resolution</h1>
            <p>
                Routine decisions are made by managers.
            
                Club-level decisions are made by supervisors with member input.
              
                Major issues escalate to founders.
                
                Disputes follow a clear escalation path: Supervisor → Manager → Founder.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec10">
            <h1>X - Amendments</h1>
            <p>Amendments require approval from both founders.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="info-sec" id="info-sec11">
            <h1>XI - Future Growth</h1>
            <p>The structure will evolve as Junto grows, adding managers and refining processes while always respecting founders’ authority.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>